{"type":"message","id":"d09b5bdf","parentId":"b64049cb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:39:49.316Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ra1daem4rsvd_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5285\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2239\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2239\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 053914 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight creates a concrete path: implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) to classify pulse content as invariant (causal) or variant (session-specific). The pulse logs in `logs/` contain the data needed to validate this hypothesis.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"rapid-otter","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5285\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2239\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2239\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 053914 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight creates a concrete path: implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) to classify pulse content as invariant (causal) or variant (session-specific). The pulse logs in `logs/` contain the data needed to validate this hypothesis.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774345189314}}
{"type":"message","id":"b7ed1447","parentId":"d09b5bdf","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:39:49.318Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ra1daem4rsvd_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 053727\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- Key insight: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- Next action: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier\r\n- Need to: Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files, measure accuracy\r\n\r\nThe most impactful next action is to implement the TIC classifier. Let me look at what exists:\r\n\r\n1. `logs/pulse_*.md` files exist (pulse logs)\r\n2. Need to implement a TIC classifier that:\r\n   - Classifies pulse content as invariant or variant\r\n   - Predicts next pulse content from invariants\r\n   - Measures >70% classification accuracy and >60% prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nI should create a script or implementation for the TIC classifier. Given the PowerShell environment, I could create:\r\n1. A PowerShell script for the TIC classifier\r\n2. Or document the algorithm\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending actions:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define `significance` scoring\r\n- Implement TIC classifier\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to implement the TIC classifier on the pulse logs. I should create a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC experiment script that analyzes the pulse logs to find invariants and variants.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. The pulse logs already exist and contain the data needed to test this hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation script that analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns and attempts next-pulse prediction. This directly advances the Phase 1 unification goal.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Validates COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 20,        # Number of recent pulses to analyze\r\n    [int]$MinFreq = 3,          # Minimum occurrences for invariant classification\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs in chronological order\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path . -Filter $LogPattern | Sort-Object Name | Select-Object -Last $Lookback\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Analyzing $($pulseFiles.Count) recent pulses...\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Min frequency threshold for invariance: $MinFreq\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"[FAIL] Insufficient pulse logs for TIC experiment\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Phase 1: Extract n-grams from each pulse\r\nfunction Get-NGrams {\r\n    param([string]$Text, [int]$N = 3)\r\n    $tokens = $Text -split '\\s+' | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 2 }\r\n    $ngrams = @()\r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -le $tokens.Count - $N; $i++) {\r\n        $ngrams += ($tokens[$i..($i + $N - 1)] -join ' ').ToLower()\r\n    }\r\n    return $ngrams\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Phase 2: Build frequency map across all pulses\r\n$globalFreq = @{}\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    $ngrams = Get-NGrams $content\r\n    foreach ($ng in $ngrams) {\r\n        if ($globalFreq.ContainsKey($ng)) {\r\n            $globalFreq[$ng]++\r\n        } else {\r\n            $globalFreq[$ng] = 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Phase 3: Classify each pulse as invariant-heavy or variant-heavy\r\n$pulseResults = @()\r\n$invariantNgrams = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    $ngrams = Get-NGrams $content\r\n    \r\n    $invariants = @()\r\n    $variants = @()\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($ng in $ngrams) {\r\n        if ($globalFreq[$ng] -ge $MinFreq) {\r\n            $invariants += $ng\r\n        } else {\r\n            $variants += $ng\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $invRatio = if ($ngrams.Count -gt 0) { $invariants.Count / $ngrams.Count } else { 0 }\r\n    \r\n    $pulseResults += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File = $file.Name\r\n        InvariantRatio = [math]::Round($invRatio, 3)\r\n        InvariantCount = $invariants.Count\r\n        VariantCount = $variants.Count\r\n        IsInvariantHeavy = ($invRatio -gt 0.5)\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    if ($invRatio -gt 0.5) {\r\n        $invariantNgrams += $invariants | Select-Object -Unique\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Phase 4: Next-pulse prediction test\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Next-Pulse Prediction Test ===\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\n$correct = 0\r\n$total = 0\r\n\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $pulseResults.Count - 1; $i++) {\r\n    $current = $pulseResults[$i]\r\n    $next =\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 05:38:02\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774345189316}}
