{"type":"message","id":"a4314ee3","parentId":"0783cc62","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:39:57.932Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_11e9ljummurn_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5285\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2239\n[mutation parse failed] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2239\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 053914 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight creates a concrete path: implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) to classify pulse content as invariant (causal) or variant (session-specific). The pulse logs in `logs/` contain the data needed to validate this hypothesis."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"rapid-otter","total":4,"totalLines":4,"totalChars":467,"truncated":false,"exitCode":0,"name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774345197930}}
