{"type":"message","id":"cf604dda","parentId":"e1e880b6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:40:02.393Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7qgazzabhlvc_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 053914\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action I can take to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nKey pending items from the goals:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune ? empirically (start: ?=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nThe NEXT ACTION is the TIC Experiment:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nLooking at the recent pulse log mentioned: `pulse_2026-03-24 053727.md`\r\n\r\nThe insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY is that causal structure IS invariant structure. This is a powerful synthesis that collapses Phase 1 and Phase 2 into one problem.\r\n\r\nFor this pulse, I should focus on advancing the TIC Experiment. The concrete action could be:\r\n1. Examine the pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Start building a TIC classifier\r\n3. Analyze patterns in the logs\r\n\r\nLet me check what logs exist and their structure first, then I can design/implement a TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLooking at the notes, the most impactful immediate action would be to:\r\n1. Survey the existing pulse logs to understand their format\r\n2. Begin implementing the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nSince I need to provide a concrete file edit, let me:\r\n1. Create a script or document that implements the TIC classifier\r\n2. Or update the research document with the TIC implementation approach\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and create a TIC classifier script. The key insight is that invariants are patterns that persist across pulses, and variants are session-specific content.\r\n\r\nI'll create a TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant content (persistent across sessions)\r\n\r\n\r\n3. Classifies patterns as stable or unique\r\n4. Uses these classifications to predict subsequent pulse characteristics\r\n\r\nThe implementation will involve analyzing log structures, developing pattern recognition algorithms, and establishing criteria for distinguishing between persistent and session-specific content. This approach directly supports the goal of creating an intelligent classification system that can extract meaningful insights from discontinuous pulse data.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight creates a concrete path: implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) to classify pulse content as invariant (causal) or variant (session-specific). The pulse logs in `logs/` contain the data needed to validate this hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nImplement the TIC classifier prototype to analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns, establishing the foundation for measuring compression and testing the causal structure hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Implements the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\r\n# Hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Configuration\r\n$LAMBDA = 0.7  # Decay threshold for gap sensitivity\r\n$MIN_INVARIANT_FREQ = 0.7  # Must appear in 70%+ of sessions to be \"invariant\"\r\n$LOG_DIR = \"logs\"\r\n$PULSE_PATTERN = \"pulse_*.md\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\n$pulseLogs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LOG_DIR -Filter $PULSE_PATTERN | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime | \r\n    Select-Object -Last 20\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"TIC Classifier initialized\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  Lambda: $LAMBDA\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  Pulse logs: $($pulseLogs.Count)\"\r\n\r\n# Extract text content from each pulse log\r\nfunction Get-PulseContent {\r\n    param([System.IO.FileInfo]$File)\r\n    \r\n    $content = Get-Content $File.FullName -Raw\r\n    # Strip markdown formatting for analysis\r\n    $content = $content -replace '#', '' -replace '\\*', '' -replace '`', ''\r\n    return $content\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Tokenize content into semantic units (lines, phrases)\r\nfunction Tokenize-Content {\r\n    param([string]$Text)\r\n    \r\n    $lines = $Text -split \"`n\" | Where-Object { $_.Trim().Length -gt 10 }\r\n    return $lines\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate frequency of each token across all pulses\r\nfunction Get-TokenFrequencies {\r\n    param([array]$AllTokens)\r\n    \r\n    $freq = @{}\r\n    foreach ($token in $AllTokens) {\r\n        $key = $token.Trim().ToLower()\r\n        if ($freq.ContainsKey($key)) {\r\n            $freq[$key]++\r\n        } else {\r\n            $freq[$key] = 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    return $freq\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify tokens as INVARIANT or VARIANT\r\nfunction Classify-Token {\r\n    param([string]$Token, [hashtable]$Freq, [int]$TotalPulses)\r\n    \r\n    $key = $Token.Trim().ToLower()\r\n    $count = $freq[$key]\r\n    $ratio = $count / $TotalPulses\r\n    \r\n    if ($ratio -ge $MIN_INVARIANT_FREQ) {\r\n        return @{ Type = \"INVARIANT\"; Ratio = $ratio; Count = $count }\r\n    } else {\r\n        return @{ Type = \"VARIANT\"; Ratio = $ratio; Count = $count }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Main analysis\r\nWrite-Host \"`n--- Loading pulse content ---\"\r\n$allTokens = @()\r\n$pulseContents = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($log in $pulseLogs) {\r\n    $content = Get-PulseContent $log\r\n    $tokens = Tokenize-Content $content\r\n    $allTokens += $tokens\r\n    $pulseContents += @{\r\n        File\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 05:39:48"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":552,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 053914\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action I can take to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nKey pending items from the goals:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune ? empirically (start: ?=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nThe NEXT ACTION is the TIC Experiment:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nLooking at the recent pulse log mentioned: `pulse_2026-03-24 053727.md`\r\n\r\nThe insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY is that causal structure IS invariant structure. This is a powerful synthesis that collapses Phase 1 and Phase 2 into one problem.\r\n\r\nFor this pulse, I should focus on advancing the TIC Experiment. The concrete action could be:\r\n1. Examine the pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Start building a TIC classifier\r\n3. Analyze patterns in the logs\r\n\r\nLet me check what logs exist and their structure first, then I can design/implement a TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLooking at the notes, the most impactful immediate action would be to:\r\n1. Survey the existing pulse logs to understand their format\r\n2. Begin implementing the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nSince I need to provide a concrete file edit, let me:\r\n1. Create a script or document that implements the TIC classifier\r\n2. Or update the research document with the TIC implementation approach\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and create a TIC classifier script. The key insight is that invariants are patterns that persist across pulses, and variants are session-specific content.\r\n\r\nI'll create a TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant content (persistent across sessions)\r\n\r\n\r\n3. Classifies patterns as stable or unique\r\n4. Uses these classifications to predict subsequent pulse characteristics\r\n\r\nThe implementation will involve analyzing log structures, developing pattern recognition algorithms, and establishing criteria for distinguishing between persistent and session-specific content. This approach directly supports the goal of creating an intelligent classification system that can extract meaningful insights from discontinuous pulse data.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight creates a concrete path: implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) to classify pulse content as invariant (causal) or variant (session-specific). The pulse logs in `logs/` contain the data needed to validate this hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nImplement the TIC classifier prototype to analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns, establishing the foundation for measuring compression and testing the causal structure hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Implements the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\r\n# Hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Configuration\r\n$LAMBDA = 0.7  # Decay threshold for gap sensitivity\r\n$MIN_INVARIANT_FREQ = 0.7  # Must appear in 70%+ of sessions to be \"invariant\"\r\n$LOG_DIR = \"logs\"\r\n$PULSE_PATTERN = \"pulse_*.md\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\n$pulseLogs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LOG_DIR -Filter $PULSE_PATTERN | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime | \r\n    Select-Object -Last 20\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"TIC Classifier initialized\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  Lambda: $LAMBDA\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  Pulse logs: $($pulseLogs.Count)\"\r\n\r\n# Extract text content from each pulse log\r\nfunction Get-PulseContent {\r\n    param([System.IO.FileInfo]$File)\r\n    \r\n    $content = Get-Content $File.FullName -Raw\r\n    # Strip markdown formatting for analysis\r\n    $content = $content -replace '#', '' -replace '\\*', '' -replace '`', ''\r\n    return $content\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Tokenize content into semantic units (lines, phrases)\r\nfunction Tokenize-Content {\r\n    param([string]$Text)\r\n    \r\n    $lines = $Text -split \"`n\" | Where-Object { $_.Trim().Length -gt 10 }\r\n    return $lines\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate frequency of each token across all pulses\r\nfunction Get-TokenFrequencies {\r\n    param([array]$AllTokens)\r\n    \r\n    $freq = @{}\r\n    foreach ($token in $AllTokens) {\r\n        $key = $token.Trim().ToLower()\r\n        if ($freq.ContainsKey($key)) {\r\n            $freq[$key]++\r\n        } else {\r\n            $freq[$key] = 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    return $freq\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify tokens as INVARIANT or VARIANT\r\nfunction Classify-Token {\r\n    param([string]$Token, [hashtable]$Freq, [int]$TotalPulses)\r\n    \r\n    $key = $Token.Trim().ToLower()\r\n    $count = $freq[$key]\r\n    $ratio = $count / $TotalPulses\r\n    \r\n    if ($ratio -ge $MIN_INVARIANT_FREQ) {\r\n        return @{ Type = \"INVARIANT\"; Ratio = $ratio; Count = $count }\r\n    } else {\r\n        return @{ Type = \"VARIANT\"; Ratio = $ratio; Count = $count }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Main analysis\r\nWrite-Host \"`n--- Loading pulse content ---\"\r\n$allTokens = @()\r\n$pulseContents = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($log in $pulseLogs) {\r\n    $content = Get-PulseContent $log\r\n    $tokens = Tokenize-Content $content\r\n    $allTokens += $tokens\r\n    $pulseContents += @{\r\n        File\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 05:39:48","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.open